node.text:
Hey StarReaders! 😉 ⭐ 
We hope you didn't miss our first & second episode from the Star Stable Master Class with author @helenadahlgrenofficial. Here's the first episode for you to learn from now or save for later, to enjoy during your cozy weekend! 📖

If you've already dived into our Star Stable Master Class, we're happy to let you know that Episodes 3 & 4 will come out soon, stay tuned! 🤩

Not only is this Star Stable Master Class full of awesome advice, but we hope it encourages you to write your own story! Put your learnings to the test by joining our ongoing storytelling challenge. Take part in our short
story competition for the chance to have your story turned into an
Instagram comic by illustrator Elli Puukangaas! @ellipuukangas #SSOStoryTellers #ReadWriteUnite

node.title: Star Stable Master Class: From reader to writer

Hey StarFam! The all-new American Paint has arrived!
There’s nothing quite like a horse and rider roaming freely together, with nothing else before them but inviting grassy plains and the backdrop of a snow-capped mountain range. For the American Paint Horse, this is where they’re in their element. The American Paint horse shares a close ancestry with other popular North American breeds like the American Quarter Horse and American Thoroughbred and therefore shares their long history of aiding humans in shaping North America into the land it is today. They’re strong and easygoing as well as intelligent, making them a fun and rewarding breed to train. Are you ready to bond with this reliable roamer of the American plains? #ColorMePaint

★ Where can I get it?
The Riding Hall! This is a temporary location for now. We’ll find them a permanent place in a later update.
★ How much does it cost?
850 Star Coins.
★ What colors can I choose from?
Dark Bay Tobiano, Chestnut Overo, Black Tobiano, Buckskin Tobiano, Grullo Tobiano, and Dapple Grey Tobiano.

We have new tack to pair with your Paint! With its renowned history in North America and western events, these recolors of Western tack suit the Paint perfectly. There are four matching sets with new halters, blankets, boots, and saddles! Find them at the Global Store and tack store at Starshine Ranch.

Keep on reading at starstable.com to find out more about this week’s update!

Hey StarFam! This week Yelena is bringing you a new Working Equitation race in Silverglade and a new item can be found at the Moorland Bonus Shop for Pay-Once Star Riders!

This race is a tribute to Yelena’s most-loved sport! Haven’t heard of Working Equitation? It celebrates the cooperation between horse and rider while overcoming different obstacles—inspired by traditional work performed on horseback on the ranch. The speed trial is Yelena’s favorite part and this race honors just that! Now she is looking for skilled riders to take on a new race that will be a little more challenging than her first!

Keep on reading at starstable.com to find out more about this week’s update!

Hey StarFam! Exciting news—Riding Clubs get access to their very own Riding Hall! Enter your Riding Hall in style with new Mix-n-Match items.

In Jorvik, the special bond of friendship makes the island a wonderful place to be. We think the bond amongst Club Members is something to be celebrated! So from now on, you get access to a private Riding Hall for you and your club. Use it for whatever your heart desires: casual meetup, planning, or practicing routines.

The Club Riding Hall looks exactly like the Riding Hall that was unveiled last week. That means you can choose between preplaced props, dance in the stands, listen to brand-new Star Stable music, pick outfits in your dressing room, change your horse’s mane style...the list goes on! We also added another prop board that is exclusive to the Club Riding Hall. Choose between three Western-themed prop sets: trail, barrel racing, and pole bending.

How about matching your Riding Club Members while you’re there? A shipment of the Sunset Trails riding set just arrived in four new colors! They’re on display and ready to purchase in the Global Store and the shops in Dundull!

Lastly, a water update! The water in Jorvik has been beautifully updated. You can see reflections on the surface and refractions in shallow water. But you have to turn the feature on to see it! Go to “Settings”, then “Graphics”, then check the box titled “Reflections” to see the updated look. This might slow down performance a bit, so it is up to you if you want to leave it on or off!

Keep on reading at starstable.com to find out more about this week’s update!
